thread.title: Irish women open up about abortion before vote

title: Irish women open up about abortion before vote
text:
Irish women open up about abortion before vote 1:40pm EDT - 01:45
When a 'licence to kill' anti-abortion poster went up outside her house in Dublin, Amy Callahan decided to speak out about travelling to England for an abortion. She's one of many women opening up about their termination experiences before an Irish referendum this month.
